{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab {\b System Design:} Designed and built a data recording system for real time biological and video signal acquisition. Used PTC Pro Engineer to design and print 3D parts as needed. The system monitored a force sensor to automatically detect a behavioral task and store data using a FIFO buffer.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab {\b Supervised Learning (Classification):} Classified forelimb extension and flexion movements using spinal cord signals recorded in rats. LDA, KNN, SVM, Nai\u776?ve Bayes, and Random Forest algorithms were tested and compared for their classification performance.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab {\b Supervised Learning (Regression):} Forelimb electromyography (EMG) signals were predicted from the spinal cord signals in rats. Multiple Linear Regression algorithm was used.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab {\b Image Processing:} Video images of test subjects (rats) analyzed for movement identification. Custom written MATLAB scripts were used to read and analyze video recordings frame by frame.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab {\b Academic:} Published research papers and presented academic work in national and international conferences. Tutored high school, undergraduate, and graduate students in summer research and school projects.\sa180\par}
